[thinking] **Exploring HashMap registration**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering the registration of HashMap fields. For the native aspect, it seems like it needs to be explicitly registered. I wonder if standard Java classes get registered automatically. In examples, they often use java.util.HashMap because the BasicAuthCache serializes it. But perhaps it's also linked to the class object being top-level? There are a lot of details here to think through, and I want to make sure I'm getting it right!
